Movie recommendation system¶

Often, the question of different aspects of business including the reduction of customer attrition, expansion of market share, increment of sales, etcetera, are based on various approaches as adopted by the underlying business. Such approaches might include but not limited to, conducting marketing campaigns tailored for various market segments, adoption of current customer satisfaction practices, use of recommendation tools, etc.

Primarily, recommender systems as observed by Shetty [1], help users discover new movieIds as well as services. This implies that, a recommender system ought to be configured such that they recommend the best movieId (that is, most relevant movieId based on user interactions). To this end, recommender systems are essential especially in today’s world where most of the goods and services are digitalized which often leads to users being overwhelmed by choice and need help finding what they're looking for. The ease of recommendation will often lead to more satisfied users and hence more sales. Uses of Recommender systems Some of the applications of recommender systems include, recommending movies, music, television programs, books, documents, websites, conferences, tourism scenic spots and learning materials.

Objective¶

In practice, there are quite a number of recommender systems which are broadly categorized into traditional and modern recommender systems. In an article by Sciforce blog [2], it is noted that traditional recommender systems (RSs) include content-based and collaborative filtering (CF) systems grounding their recommendations on historical interactions and user/item attributes. Content-based recommendations are mainly drawn on the user’s item and profile features, and CF seeks a similar audience’s preferences. On the other hand, modern recommender systems are mainly based on deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which [2] observes as being a good fit for unstructured multimedia data processing given effective feature extraction.

Research Objective¶

The current study proposes a deep learning based recommender systems for the recommendation of movies based on an individual’s previous movie ratings. Moreover, the proposed recommender system will be based on the web UI that is proposed to be developed using Django .

Simple Cosine Similarity¶

Doing this in chunks for the test set so that we don't run into memory issues. For the recall measure, if the track's relative percentile is < 0.5 then its a 1

In [861]:
# Simple Cosine Similarity
from scipy.stats import percentileofscore
def simple_cosine(data, pred):
    from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
    #Cosine similarity model to generate a matrix and determine the closest recommendation depending on the similarity matrix
    
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    # implement cosine similarity
    sim = cosine_similarity(scaled_df.transpose(), dense_output=False)
    sim[np.diag_indices(sim.shape[0])] = 0
    denom = np.asarray(sim.sum(axis=1)).reshape(-1)

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values

    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(scaled_df.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (scaled_df[indexx].dot(sim)) / denom
        score = (-score).argsort() / denom.shape[0]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

def neural_network_model(number_of_users, num_items, latent_dim, regs=[0,0]):
    # model vars
    user_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'user_input')
    item_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'item_input')

    MF_Embedding_User = Embedding(input_dim = number_of_users, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'user_embedding', 
                                  embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[0]), input_length=1)
    MF_Embedding_Item = Embedding(input_dim = num_items, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'item_embedding',
                                  embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[1]), input_length=1)   
    
    # essential to define an embedding vector!
    user_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_User(user_input))
    item_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_Item(item_input))
    
    # user-item embedding productper element
    predict_vector = merge.Multiply()([user_latent, item_latent])
    
    # Final prediction layer
    prediction = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer='lecun_uniform', name = 'prediction')(predict_vector)
    
    model = Model(inputs=[user_input, item_input], outputs=prediction)

    return model

# create the model
def recall(y_true, y_pred):
    tp = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true * y_pred, 0, 1)))
    pos_pt = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true, 0, 1)))
    recall = tp / (pos_pt + K.epsilon())
    return recall

model = neural_network_model(n_users, num_of_items, 50, regs = [0,0])

    print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
    cross_movieId = np.transpose([np.tile(np.arange(num_of_items), len(indexx)), np.repeat(indexx, len(np.arange(num_of_items)))])
    score = model.predict([cross_movieId[:,1], cross_movieId[:,0]], batch_size=50000, verbose=1).reshape(indexx.shape[0], num_of_items)

    sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
    chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
    res.append(chunk_score)
    prev_max = indexx.max() + 1

Non-Negative Matrix Factorization¶

In [722]:
def nmf_model(data, pred, model):
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    W = model.fit_transform(scaled_df)
    H = model.components_

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values
    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(W.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (W[indexx].dot(H))
        score = (-score).argsort() / score.shape[1]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

K = 2

# NMF
#NNDSVD with zeros filled with the average of X (better when sparsity is not desired)
model = NMF(n_components = K, init = 'nndsvd', max_iter = 1000, tol = 0.1, random_state = 1)
Recommendations1 = nmf_model(train_df, testw, model)
mpr_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization = Recommendations1.sum()/len(testw)

Simple Cosine Similarity¶

Doing this in chunks for the test set so that we don't run into memory issues. For the recall measure, if the track's relative percentile is < 0.5 then its a 1

In [154]:
# Simple Cosine Similarity
from scipy.stats import percentileofscore
def simple_cosine(data, pred):
    from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
    #Cosine similarity model to generate a matrix and determine the closest recommendation depending on the similarity matrix
    
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    # implement cosine similarity
    sim = cosine_similarity(scaled_df.transpose(), dense_output=False)
    sim[np.diag_indices(sim.shape[0])] = 0
    denom = np.asarray(sim.sum(axis=1)).reshape(-1)

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values

    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(scaled_df.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (scaled_df[indexx].dot(sim)) / denom
        score = (-score).argsort() / denom.shape[0]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

def neural_network_model(number_of_users, num_items, latent_dim, regs=[0,0]):
    # model vars
    user_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'user_input')
    item_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'item_input')

    MF_Embedding_User = Embedding(input_dim = number_of_users, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'user_embedding', 
                                  embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[0]), input_length=1)
    MF_Embedding_Item = Embedding(input_dim = num_items, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'item_embedding',
                                  embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[1]), input_length=1)   
    
    # essential to define an embedding vector!
    user_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_User(user_input))
    item_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_Item(item_input))
    
    # user-item embedding productper element
    predict_vector = merge.Multiply()([user_latent, item_latent])
    
    # Final prediction layer
    prediction = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer='lecun_uniform', name = 'prediction')(predict_vector)
    
    model = Model(inputs=[user_input, item_input], outputs=prediction)

    return model

# create the model
def recall(y_true, y_pred):
    tp = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true * y_pred, 0, 1)))
    pos_pt = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true, 0, 1)))
    recall = tp / (pos_pt + K.epsilon())
    return recall

model = neural_network_model(n_users, num_of_items, 50, regs = [0,0])

Non-Negative Matrix Factorization¶

In [ ]:
def nmf_model(data, pred, model):
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    W = model.fit_transform(scaled_df)
    H = model.components_

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values
    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(W.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (W[indexx].dot(H))
        score = (-score).argsort() / score.shape[1]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

K = 2

# NMF
#NNDSVD with zeros filled with the average of X (better when sparsity is not desired)
model = NMF(n_components = K, init = 'nndsvd', max_iter = 1000, tol = 0.1, random_state = 1)
Recommendations1 = nmf_model(train_df, testw, model)
mpr_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization = Recommendations1.sum()/len(testw)

# Simple Cosine Similarity

def simple_cosine(data, pred):
    from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
    #Cosine similarity model to generate a matrix and determine the closest recommendation depending on the similarity matrix
    
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    # implement cosine similarity
    sim = cosine_similarity(scaled_df.transpose(), dense_output=False)
    sim[np.diag_indices(sim.shape[0])] = 0
    denom = np.asarray(sim.sum(axis=1)).reshape(-1)

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values

    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(scaled_df.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (scaled_df[indexx].dot(sim)) / denom
        score = (-score).argsort() / denom.shape[0]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

def neural_network_model(number_of_users, num_items, latent_dim, regs=[0,0]):
    # model vars
    user_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'user_input')
    item_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32', name = 'item_input')

    MF_Embedding_User = Embedding(input_dim = number_of_users, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'user_embedding', embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[0]), input_length=1)
    MF_Embedding_Item = Embedding(input_dim = num_items, output_dim = latent_dim, name = 'item_embedding', embeddings_regularizer = l2(regs[1]), input_length=1)   
    
    # essential to define an embedding vector!
    user_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_User(user_input))
    item_latent = Flatten()(MF_Embedding_Item(item_input))
    
    # user-item embedding productper element
    predict_vector = merge.Multiply()([user_latent, item_latent])
    
    # Final prediction layer
    prediction = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer='lecun_uniform', name = 'prediction')(predict_vector)
    
    model = Model(inputs=[user_input, item_input], outputs=prediction)

    return model

# create the model
def recall(y_true, y_pred):
    tp = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true * y_pred, 0, 1)))
    pos_pt = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true, 0, 1)))
    recall = tp / (pos_pt + K.epsilon())
    return recall

model = neural_network_model(n_users, num_of_items, 50, regs = [0,0])

# compute MPR
# we implement per chunk to handle memory issues
user_index = testw['userId'].cat.codes.values
item_index = testw['movieId'].cat.codes.values
number_of_chunks = 10
chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(n_users), number_of_chunks)
res = []
prev_max = 0
for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
    print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
    cross_movieId = np.transpose([np.tile(np.arange(num_of_items), len(indexx)), np.repeat(indexx, len(np.arange(num_of_items)))])
    score = model.predict([cross_movieId[:,1], cross_movieId[:,0]], batch_size=50000, verbose=1).reshape(indexx.shape[0], num_of_items)
    score = (-score).argsort() / score.shape[1]
    sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
    chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
    res.append(chunk_score)
    prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
mpr_NCF = np.concatenate(res).sum()/len(testw)
print(f'NCF MPR: {mpr_NCF:.5f}')
rec_NCF = (np.concatenate(res) < 0.5).sum()/len(testw)
print(f'NCF Model Recall rate: {rec_NCF:.5f}')

def nmf_model(data, pred, model):
    # normalize to obtain the % importance to user
    scaled_df = data.multiply(1/data.sum(axis=1)).tocsr()
    W = model.fit_transform(scaled_df)
    H = model.components_

    # implement per chunk to handle memory issues
    user_index = pred['userId'].cat.codes.values
    item_index = pred['movieId'].cat.codes.values
    number_of_chunks = 30
    chunks = np.array_split(np.arange(W.shape[0]), number_of_chunks)
    res = []
    prev_max = 0
    for i,indexx in enumerate(chunks):
        print(f'Implementing chunk : {i+1}/{number_of_chunks}')
        score = (W[indexx].dot(H))
        score = (-score).argsort() / score.shape[1]
        sel = (user_index >= indexx.min()) & (user_index <= indexx.max())
        chunk_score = np.asarray(score[user_index[sel] - prev_max, item_index[sel]]).reshape(-1)
        res.append(chunk_score)
        prev_max = indexx.max() + 1
    return np.concatenate(res)

K = 2

# NMF
model = NMF(n_components = K, init = 'nndsvd', max_iter = 1000, tol = 0.1)
Recommendations1 = nmf_model(train_df, testw, model)
mpr_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization = Recommendations1.sum()/len(testw)
print(f'NMF MPR: {mpr_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization:.5f}')
rec_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization = (Recommendations1 < 0.5).sum()/len(testw)
print(f'Model Recall rate: {rec_Non_Negative_Matrix_Factorization:.5f}')
